foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: During this fiscal year 2014, DOL located 550 FOIA requests that were received during FY 2013 but were not converted for processing and tracking purposes within the FOIA tracking system and, therefore, were not included in last year's report. The Numbers of Requests Pending as of the start of the Fiscal Year have been corrected from the number of requests reported as pending at the end of Fiscal Year 2013.

foia:OldestPendingRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: Some work day ranges reported appear to be out of sequence based on the date of the receipt of the request. However, this is attributed to requests that have been "tolled" for clarification or to resolve fee matters consistent with the provisions of the statute.

As noted DOL located 550 initial FOIA requests that remained pending in the Departmental FOIA tracking system and requiring further action, many of which were received in prior years. Accordingly, DOL has identified 8 additional intial FOIA requests that should have been previously reported and are now among the 10 oldest pending requests.

foia:ProcessedConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: As a part of the audit of data in Departmental FOIA tracking system, DOL located 557 requests that remained pending in the system and requiring further action, many of which were received in prior years. Among those is one consultation, originating with OWCP, which should have been previously reported.

foia:ProcessedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: The numbers of request received and processed during the fiscal year from last year's annual report have been corrected.

foia:BackloggedAppealComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: In 2013 Annual FOIA, DOL reported 183 backlogged FOIA Appeals. That number was tabulated incorrectly. We are correcting that number here to reflect that there were actually 186 FOIA appeals that were backlogged at the end of FY2013.
